{"questionId":"26697","questionHtml":"<p>A ray of light is incident on the flat side of a semi-circular glass block placed in paraffin.&nbsp;The ray is totally internally reflected inside the glass block as shown.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/501fbe30d7ac8ce70d9cc8aa1c8372797e1e8be2.png\"></p>\n<p>The refractive index of glass is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and the refractive index of paraffin is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>What is correct?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"26697","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.17","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A ray of light is incident on the flat side of a semi-circular glass block placed in paraffin. The ray is totally internally reflected inside the glass block as shown. The refracti","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"17","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.4 – Wave behaviour","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}